Installation Git
----------------

Step1: Update you linux system by using command
## yum update -y

Step2: Install the git by using command
## yum install git -y

Step3: Check the Version
## git --version

Step4: then inzitallation the git by command 
## git init

Step5: git clone with git hub repository
## git clone <url>

" Then check the git hub repo is their any folder are file and create in local repo"

Step6: mkdir folder name <Project1>
	Cd project1
	"Create file in project"
	touch File1.txt

Step7: add the file in git repo using command
##  git add .

Step8 : Then commit the file into the github repo using command
## git commit -m "file is adding" <file name> File1.txt

Step8: Last step to push file  into the local repo to remote repo
## git push origin master

\\Then git is asking the crediential like your mail id and Passwd\\

